2020-2021 Senior, Briell Price, entered a scholarship through Breakthrough for school! This scholarship is an amazing opportunity with a big prize. As part of the process, she was challenged with making a 3 minute video describing my most passionate physics topic. Through the challenge, there is what’s called the “popular vote” which means that if my video gets the most likes and comments that I could win the popular vote for the region. Take a look at her video and give it a big thumbs up! Here is the link to the video https://youtu.be/dBQFyFKbe24
Please share this post so we can get her video put out to as many people as possible.

MAPLETOWN NEWS:

Dear Students,

We are currently in the process of assessing the possibility of having Prom at the Mapletown High School on July 17th. Prom will be open to all students who were in grades 9 through 12 during the 2019-2020 school year.

If you purchased a ticket already, please complete the attached Google Sheets survey. Those who do not plan on attending will be issued a refund. To receive a refund you must complete the form and enter that you do not plan to attend.



Students who wish to purchase a ticket should also complete this form and enter the number of tickets they plan on purchasing. Tickets are $50 per person.



Please complete this form by this Thursday, June 18, 2020. Once the survey is complete we will announce if we have enough participation to continue.

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1CJnX3U7RJUMSDhoHxbP5d4u3Zh-mKP8buVWraW3xB14/edit?usp=sharing

Thank you!
Mr. Reed

post_text:
MAPLETOWN HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS

Below you will find the Schedule Request Forms to choose your classes for next year please take a serious look at the document and complete it to scheduling@segsd.org or print it out and return it with your completed packets on June1-3. This year will be a unique year with its own set of obstacles and challenges, with that being said, Mr. Donley and I are working on creating the Master schedule at this time and some things may change but we will do our best to get you the classes you request. However, I will assure you we will get you the classes needed for graduation and to keep you moving forward academically.
Some of you plan to attend the CTC next year, if that is your intention please also complete the CTC application attached to this email.
Please email or call us with any questions or concerns.

Hope all is well and hope to see you soon!

Mr. Fink
text:
MAPLETOWN HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS

Below you will find the Schedule Request Forms to choose your classes for next year please take a serious look at the document and complete it to scheduling@segsd.org or print it out and return it with your completed packets on June1-3. This year will be a unique year with its own set of obstacles and challenges, with that being said, Mr. Donley and I are working on creating the Master schedule at this time and some things may change but we will do our best to get you the classes you request. However, I will assure you we will get you the classes needed for graduation and to keep you moving forward academically.
Some of you plan to attend the CTC next year, if that is your intention please also complete the CTC application attached to this email.
Please email or call us with any questions or concerns.

Hope all is well and hope to see you soon!

Mr. Fink

post_text:
Instructional packets are due the week of June 1st. Packets may be dropped off at your child’s school on Monday, June 1st through Wednesday, June 3rd from 7 am to 2 pm. The drop off at Bobtown Elementary will be at the loading dock area, and the drop off at Mapletown will be the gym lobby.

It is essential that completed packets and all classroom materials be returned during this time so that student grades may be calculated. If you are unable to drop off your packets and materials Monday, June 1st through Wednesday, June 3rd from 7 am to 2 pm, please contact the school office.

You are extremely important to society. You are the teachers of the world, you help your students find themselves. We can count on you to show us the right path. Even in the darkest of times, you are still dependable. Thank you all for being there for us, for allowing us to be ourselves, and teaching us what we need to know. Without you, no one else could get jobs because you need an education.

Thank you for choosing us,
Elizabeth Rockwell

You can learn a lot about people in a time of crisis, and I’ve learned that our faculty is strong, resilient, creative, flexible, cooperative, determined, hard-working, and caring.

You are the difference makers!

Thank you for all that you do!

Rich Pekar

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT!

Instructional packets are due the week of June 1st. Packets may be dropped off at your child’s school on Monday, June 1st through Wednesday, June 3rd from 7 am to 2 pm. The drop off at Bobtown Elementary will be at the loading dock area, and the drop off at Mapletown will be the bus entrance in front of the school.

It is essential that completed packets and all classroom materials be returned during this time so that student grades may be calculated. If you are unable to drop off your packets and materials Monday, June 1st through Wednesday, June 3rd from 7 am to 2 pm, please contact the school office.

Enrichment activities will be planned for the remainder of the year. Information about our enrichment period will be released shortly.

Dear Southeastern Greene students and parents:

Teachers have prepared educational packets for each student in our district. These packets can be picked up at your child’s school on Monday, March 30th, from 7 am to 4 pm, Tuesday, March 31st, from 8 am to 1 pm, and Wednesday, April 1st from 8 am to 1 pm. The pickup location for Bobtown is the loading dock beside the school, and Mapletown will be distributing packets by the gym lobby entrance. We further ask that everyone remains in their vehicle at all times while a staff member delivers the packets to your car. Thank you!

post_text:
Today, Governor Tom Wolf announced that all K-12 Pennsylvania schools will remain closed through at least April 6th. The closure order could be extended beyond April 6th if necessary. Our district plan is to begin instruction for students on Monday, March 30th, with instructional packets and online resources that can be completed at home with teacher support through emails and phone calls. We will be sending out more information regarding this plan later this week. The health and safety of our students and staff will always be our number one priority.

Thank you, and stay safe

post_text: Today, Governor Tom Wolf announced that all K-12 Pennsylvania schools will be closed for ten business days. The Southeastern Greene School District will close from Monday, March 16, 2020, through Friday, March 27, 2020. We will continue to suspend all extra-curricular activities, including field trips and athletics, until further notice. At the end of ten days, the situation will be re-evaluated to determine if continued closure is needed. The health and safety of our students and staff will always be our number one priority.

We will continue to suspend all extra-curricular activities, including field trips and athletics, until further notice. post_text:
The Employees of the Southeastern Greene School District raised funds again this year to purchase 40 Christmas Hams for members of the community. Several Hams will be donated to the Foodbank and several more will be delivered by the staff of the school district to individuals’ homes over the next few days.

We wish you all an enjoyable and safe Christmas and New Year with friends and family.

“Christmas is the spirit of giving without a thought of getting. It is happiness because we see the joy in people. It is forgetting self and finding time for others. It is discarding the meaningless and stressing the true values (Thomas S. Monson).”

Come and enjoy a night at Buffalo Wild Wings with Mapletown’s NHS and NJHS. Proceeds of your bill will benefit the groups’ trip to Washington D.C.

Please check out the flier for directions and time of the event. Also, must show a picture of this flier at Buffalo Wild Wings for the honor societies to get credit for the meal. All you have to do is just show up or take out, eat and that’s it!

Welcome to share the link with everyone! Thank you!

The Reorganization Meeting of the SEGSD Board of Directors was held last evening.
Swearing in of newly elected members was Mr. Andrew Vanata and Mr. Kristafer Adkins and re-elected members are Mrs. Virginia Eberhart, Mr. J.R. Antill, and Mrs. Christine Spiker.

SEGSD Board of Directors Officers for 2020 will be as follows:
Mrs. Janet Pennington - President and PSBA Representative
Mr. Gary Moser - Vice-President and CTC Representative
Mr. J.R. Antill - Treasurer
